[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police and air ambulance attend serious crash on A811

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police and the ambulance staff have attended a serious crash on the A811 near Drymen in Stirlingshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It happened near Ballat Crossroads at Balfron Station on Saturday afternoon.
An air ambulance was seen landing in a nearby field.
Police said the road was closed between the A81 at Ballat Crossroads and Drymen. Drivers were urged to use an alternative route.
